Articles.Content:
I've been collecting basic science statistics in Rocket Scientist level and found some interesting results. Eeloo and Dres are the two best locations to land and return from. You can land in different biomes to collect science which will be the same value. Eve is also equal to Eeloo in science value on land. Don't go to Eve's ocean, the science values are incredibly low/broken? 

Duna's South Pole and North Pole are both called South Pole. Should be renamed to Poles like Laythe.

TLDR: Go to Eeloo, Dres and Eve for maximum returns though I haven't tested with science collecting parts yet.

Note its an Eve launch window closing at the start of the game. If you are fast you can launch an Eve mission the first 14 days. 
No its far from optimal, but 4.5 km/s it not that much with light payload and nuclear, Moho is always more expensive. 
Atmospheric science is 600 transmitted, science jr is 1000 on surface, you can fly at 89 km for the atmospheric one, you want an heat shield and an docking port or rover seat for retrieving the science. 
You can also drop the front to land on Eve while circulating the engine and seat/docking port part for the science who has to be returned. 
Gilly is also very easy picking. Eve orbit and an discoverable on Gilly is also future missions you will unlock once you do the Duna monument. 

Its also an Moho window who closes pretty fast.
